St. Ignatius makes Faith and Love the whole Duty of a Chriſtian;
〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 . Ignat. Ep. ad Epheſ.
Faith the beginning, Love the end;
〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 , ibid. Faith the guide, Love the way: and he hardly ever recommends the one but in the Company of the other.
〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 . Clem, Alex. Strom. lib. 2. p. 384. Credam, diligam Demn & proximum, mihi caetera non ſunt neceſſaria; Tertul. de jejun. c. 2.
